                                                                                            <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>When using &amp;quot;kubernetes.rest-service.exposed.type=NodePort&amp;quot;, connection string for Rest gateway is now correctly constructed in form of &amp;quot;&amp;lt;nodeIp&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;nodePort&amp;gt;&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;&amp;lt;kubernetesApiServerUrl&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;nodePort&amp;gt;&amp;quot;. This may be a breaking change for some users.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This also introduces a new config option &amp;quot;kubernetes.rest-service.exposed.node-port-address-type&amp;quot; that lets you select &amp;quot;&amp;lt;nodeIp&amp;gt;&amp;quot; from a desired range.</customfieldvalue>

                        </customfieldvalues>
